.TH WIZARD 1 "2025-01-01" "wizard 1.0.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
wizard \- developer command spellbook

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wizard
[\fICOMMAND\fR] [ARGS]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Wizard is a modular developer command-line tool that provides spell-like
commands for common developer tasks, such as opening projects in various IDEs.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B summon <target> <path>
Summon an IDE and open the specified path.

Targets:
  idea   IntelliJ IDEA
  rider  JetBrains Rider
  vs     Visual Studio / VS Code (depending on system configuration)

.TP
.B help [command]
Show general help or command-specific help.

.TP
.B version
Show the wizard version.

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Open the current directory in IntelliJ IDEA:
.RS
wizard summon idea .
.RE

.PP
Open a project in Rider:
.RS
wizard summon rider ~/projects/app
.RE

.PP
Open a solution or folder in VS / VS Code:
.RS
wizard summon vs MySolution.sln
.RE

